<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mega Man 9 soundtrack rumor = rip off of MM2? ...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4959&amp;p=44370#p44370"><![CDATA[
Ok, I want to put this to rest once and for all. I've heard some people say that Mega Man 9's soundtrack literally rips off Mega Man 2, but I haven't yet detected an exact rip off or even a remote similarity between the two soundtracks. Sure it is a similar style, but I hear no melodies or anything directly taken from 2 and used in 9. Anyone else heard that? I believe it actually says this on the Mega Man 9 page at the Mega Man Home Page.<br /><br />"Music: 2 [2] [2] [2] [2] [2] [2]<br />    Many of the songs are from previous games—mostly Mega Man 2 (though ironically they seem to have chosen all of the really short and repetitive ones from that game). Some of the songs are rather high-pitched and repetitive (Tornado Man’s comes to mind) but the rest of the music isn’t that bad. The opening/ending is pretty nice, for example. A shame it all had to be in mono though. "<br /><br />What? Tornado Man is one of the coolest tracks in the game!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3735">GradualGames</a> — Mon Mar 16, 2009 7:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
